node.text: Our very first IG Live session with @alexchacon_official, a filmmaker and YouTuber from Texas, USA with over 355k thousand followers. We talk about Alex’s inspiring journey, from quitting medical school, selling everything he owned, and driving his motorcycle from Alaska to Argentina in 500 days. He’s traveled to over 70 countries while working on several projects with renowned brands and tourism boards all around the world. We ask Alex about his craziest travel experiences, how he grew and monetizes his following, and more! #TheGlobeWanderer #DigitalMarketerElite #digitalnomad

node.title: IG Live with Alex Chacon Part I

node.text: On today’s IG Live session, we are very excited to be interviewing @alexchacon_official, a filmmaker and YouTuber from Texas, USA with over 355k thousand followers. Alex’s journey began when he quit medical school, sold everything he had and drove his motorcycle from Alaska to Argentina in 500 days. Since then he’s traveled to over 70 countries while working on several projects with renowned brands and tourism boards all around the world. We’ll talk more about Alex’s incredible story, his craziest travel experiences, how he grew and monetizes his following, and more on our IG Live later at 9PM (+8 GMT) or 7AM EST, July 30th. See you all there! #TheGlobeWanderer #DigitalMarketerElite #digitalnomad

node.title: Drone Around the World with Alex Chacon

node.text:
FOLLOW @ecomdave for more Amazon tips

Imagine buying 500 units of a product.

Each unit cost $3, Which means you spent $1,500

You spend $500 to ship the product from China to Amazon warehouses.

Total investment of $2,000

You sell that product for $20 per unit.

Amazon then packages and ships your product to its customers all over the world.

500 units at a $20 a pop means $10,000 in total revenue

After Amazon takes its 25% in fees

We are left with $7,500 in revenue

After our initial product cost of $2,000

We are left with $5,500 profit from one product.

Learn the Exact Step-by-Step Process
Follow @ecomdave

node.text:
Caption and Captured by @jackson.groves Let's spend more nights under the stars in sleeping bags on top of mountains ⭐️ This is the summit of Mount Longido 2,629m. With 1300m+ of elevation and climbing through the jungle you'll reach a summit where few go. We set up our tents and enjoyed an amazing sunset while looking out at Mount Kilimanjaro, Mount Meru and across the nearby border to Kenya. In the morning we woke to an epic sunrise which is when I shot this little video of @pema.travels bundled up, taking it all in ☀️ On expedition in Tanzania with @altezza.travel 
Music by Xavier Rudd - Follow the sun
#TheGlobeWanderee
